#!/bin/bash

# inform the user how to use the image
cat <<EOF
This is a CentOS S2I image with RVM preinstalled ready to run on OpenShift
For more information about RVM: https://rvm.io

To install a specific ruby version, set environment variable RUBY_VERSION
or specify it in your Gemfile. Otherwise the rvm default ruby will be installed.

To run commands in your docker, create a Procfile and set PROCTYPE
environment variable to the command name
For more information about Procfile: https://ddollar.github.io/foreman/#PROCFILE
The web command will launch on port 8080
EOF